```

---

# Step 9 — Create index.html

```bash
nano index.html
```

Add:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Kutu DB App</title>
</head>
<body>

<h2>Add User</h2>

<input type="text" id="name" placeholder="Enter name">

<button onclick="addUser()">Submit</button>

<h2>Users</h2>

<ul id="users"></ul>

<script>

async function addUser() {

    const name = document.getElementById('name').value;

    await fetch('http://<You_local_host_name>:5000/add-user', {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: {
            'Content-Type': 'application/json'
        },
        body: JSON.stringify({ name })
    });

    loadUsers();
}

async function loadUsers() {

    const response = await fetch('http://<You_local_host_name>:5000/users');

    const users = await response.json();

    const list = document.getElementById('users');

    list.innerHTML = '';

    users.forEach(user => {

        const li = document.createElement('li');

        li.innerText = user.name;

        list.appendChild(li);
    });
}

loadUsers();

</script>

</body>
</html>
```

---

# Step 10 — Create Frontend Dockerfile

```bash
nano Dockerfile
```

Add:

```dockerfile
FROM nginx:alpine

COPY index.html /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html

EXPOSE 80

CMD ["nginx", "-g", "daemon off;"]
```

---

# Step 11 — Build Frontend Image

```bash
docker build -t kutu-db-frontend .
```

---

# Step 12 — Create PostgreSQL Volume

```bash
docker volume create postgres-data
```

---

# Step 13 — Run PostgreSQL Container

```bash
docker run -d \
--name postgres-container \
-e POSTGRES_USER=admin \
-e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=admin123 \
-e POSTGRES_DB=kutu_db \
-p 5432:5432 \
-v postgres-data:/var/lib/postgresql/data \
postgres:16
```

---

# Step 14 — Run Backend Container

Go to backend folder:

```bash
cd ../backend
```

Run:

```bash
docker run -d \
--name backend-container \
-p 5000:5000 \
--add-host=host.docker.internal:host-gateway \
kutu-db-backend
```

---

# Step 15 — Run Frontend Container

Go to frontend folder:

```bash
cd ../frontend
```

Run:

```bash
docker run -d \
--name frontend-container \
-p 8080:80 \
kutu-db-frontend
```

---

# Step 16 — Open Website

Open:

```text
http://localhost:8080
```

OR:

```text
http://YOUR_VM_IP:8080
```

---

# Step 17 — Test Persistence

Add some users.

Then remove containers:

```bash
docker rm -f frontend-container backend-container postgres-container
```

---

# Step 18 — Recreate Containers

Run PostgreSQL again:

```bash
docker run -d \
--name postgres-container \
-e POSTGRES_USER=admin \
-e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=admin123 \
-e POSTGRES_DB=kutu_db \
-p 5432:5432 \
-v postgres-data:/var/lib/postgresql/data \
postgres:16
```

Run backend:

```bash
docker run -d \
--name backend-container \
-p 5000:5000 \
--add-host=host.docker.internal:host-gateway \
kutu-db-backend
```

Run frontend:

```bash
docker run -d \
--name frontend-container \
-p 8080:80 \
kutu-db-frontend
```

---

# Final Result

Open website again.

Your previously entered users should STILL exist.

That proves:

```text
Docker volume persisted PostgreSQL database data.
```

